(Summary) Tj
T*
(Listening is a valuable part of English. Students perform better when they understand) Tj
T*
(main points, details, tone, and speaker intention, learn from examples such as) Tj
T*
(extracting key points from an oral presentation, and deliberately avoid mistakes like) Tj
T*
(hearing words without organizing the ideas. Regular practice built around listening for) Tj
T*
(gist and details makes the topic easier to remember and apply.) Tj
T*
